  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting youth and women&apos;s leadership in the struggle for urban environmental rights in Lima</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the successes of their previous project PER295, DESCO seek to make visible the demands of the peri-urban neighbourhoods of southern Lima. They will build a network of digital citizenship led by young people and women from five human settlements (H&#xE9;roes de Cenepa and Ed&#xE9;n del Manantial in the district of Villa Mar&#xED;a del Triunfo, and Halc&#xF3;n Sagrado, Vista Alegre and Capilla in the district of San Juan de Miraflores), as well as members of collectives, volunteers and activists (especially youth and women). This network will promote the right to the city and make visible urban-environmental rights, vulnerability mitigation and disaster reduction by generating actions and spaces for intergenerational dialogue, awareness-raising and influencing authorities and public opinion at the local, metropolitan, national and international levels, with a view to promoting the defence of our common home and the voices of those demanding fair and equitable access to adequate habitat.</narrative>
  </description>
